column2: This reading was taken two days after a major storm than knocked down many trees and cut power to entire area.
Beautiful weather lately- mid 70's during the day and low 50's at night.  However- yesterday was a high of 61 and a low last night of 40.

column1: We had two loon chicks born on 6/18 but unfortunately lost one this morning.

column2: 5 days of above normal temperatures raised the water temp to 80.3.
Saw a group of six loons.  Can't find our chick- afraid that it may have met its demise.
I thought we had lost the loon chick but I did observe it today.
This reading was followed by the best two hours of fishing I've ever had!
Due to numerous either rainy or windy days this is my first report of the year.  Our loon pair had two chicks but- at this point- only one has survived.

column1: The lake clarity is way down from past years.  I am assuming it is because of all the rain.  the lake water is stained but not cloudy.
